Date: Tue, 28 Apr 2026 09:39:04 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?phase9:=20wave=2013.4=20=E2=80=94=20default-ski?=
 =?UTF-8?q?p=20joystick=20init=20on=20DOS=20(patch=200065)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Wave 13.3 measurement on real HW (PODP 5V83, Cirrus + UNIVBE) left ~82
ms / flip in input_poll() unaccounted for after the SDL-side per-pump
yield was removed. Root cause: SDL3-DOS's DOS_JoystickUpdate
(vendor/SDL/src/joystick/dos/SDL_sysjoystick.c:259) runs BIOS INT 15h
gameport polling on every PumpEvents.

The Vibra16S/SB16 has an onboard gameport at I/O 0x201, so SDL3-DOS's
detection probe trips even when no physical joystick is attached. The
BIOS INT 15h call then runs the cap-discharge timing loop to its full
timeout — measured ~82 ms / flip in wave 13.3 residual.

Cave Story plays fine on keyboard. Default-skip the SDL_OpenJoystick()
call so SDL3 never polls a non-existent joystick. SDL3 only runs
driver Update functions for opened joysticks, so skipping the open
removes the entire BIOS INT 15h cost without needing any hot-path gate.

Opt back in via SET DOSKUTSU_USE_JOYSTICK=1 if a real stick is
attached. Strict "1" match (matches wave 13.2 / 13.3 helpers) so
SET FOO=0 / empty value does NOT enable.

Predicted impact: title scene 5.5 fps → ~10-12 fps on PODP 5V83
(combined with wave 13.3 yield-skip; the 33 ms shifted to flip_inner
remains, but the 82 ms BIOS gameport cost is reclaimed).

See docs/PHASE9-NEXT-WAVES-PLAN.md §6 wave 13.3 measurement table for
the residual that motivated this fix.
---
 src/input.cpp | 64 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++------------------
 1 file changed, 42 insertions(+), 22 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/input.cpp b/src/input.cpp
index 228ec5c..c829f76 100644
--- a/src/input.cpp
+++ b/src/input.cpp
@@ -107,32 +107,52 @@ bool input_init(void)
   mappings[DEBUG_FLY_KEY].key     = SDLK_V;
   mappings[ENTERKEY].key = SDLK_RETURN;
 
-  SDL_InitSubSystem(SDL_INIT_JOYSTICK);
-  // SDL3: SDL_NumJoysticks → SDL_GetJoysticks(&count) returning array of instance IDs.
-  // SDL_JoystickOpen(0) → SDL_OpenJoystick(instance_id).
-  // SDL_JoystickNameForIndex → SDL_GetJoystickNameForID.
-  // SDL_JoystickNum{Axes,Buttons,Balls} → SDL_GetNumJoystick{Axes,Buttons,Balls}.
-  int _joy_count = 0;
-  SDL_JoystickID *_joy_ids = SDL_GetJoysticks(&_joy_count);
-  if (_joy_ids && _joy_count > 0)
+  // DOS-PORT (patch 0065, Phase 9 wave 13.4): default-skip joystick init on
+  // DOS. Wave 13.3 left ~82 ms / flip unaccounted for in input_poll(); root
+  // cause is SDL3-DOS's DOS_JoystickUpdate (vendor/SDL/src/joystick/dos/
+  // SDL_sysjoystick.c:259) running BIOS INT 15h gameport polling on every
+  // PumpEvents. The Vibra16S/SB16 has an onboard gameport, so SDL3-DOS
+  // detects "joystick present" even when nothing is plugged in — the BIOS
+  // call then runs to its full cap-discharge timeout. Cave Story plays
+  // fine on keyboard; opt back in via SET DOSKUTSU_USE_JOYSTICK=1 only if
+  // a real stick is attached. Strict "1" match to avoid the wave 13.2
+  // truthiness footgun (SET FOO=0 / empty value should NOT enable).
+  const char *use_js_env = std::getenv("DOSKUTSU_USE_JOYSTICK");
+  const bool open_joystick = use_js_env && use_js_env[0] == '1' && use_js_env[1] == 0;
+  if (!open_joystick)
   {
-    SDL_JoystickID _first = _joy_ids[0];
-    joy = SDL_OpenJoystick(_first);
-
-    if (joy)
-    {
-      LOG_INFO("Opened Joystick 0");
-      LOG_INFO("Name: {}", SDL_GetJoystickNameForID(_first));
-      LOG_INFO("Number of Axes: {}", SDL_GetNumJoystickAxes(joy));
-      LOG_INFO("Number of Buttons: {}", SDL_GetNumJoystickButtons(joy));
-      LOG_INFO("Number of Balls: {}", SDL_GetNumJoystickBalls(joy));
-    }
-    else
+    LOG_INFO("Joystick: skipped (default; set DOSKUTSU_USE_JOYSTICK=1 to enable — "
+             "skips SDL3-DOS gameport BIOS INT 15h polling, ~82 ms / flip on real HW)");
+  }
+  else
+  {
+    SDL_InitSubSystem(SDL_INIT_JOYSTICK);
+    // SDL3: SDL_NumJoysticks → SDL_GetJoysticks(&count) returning array of instance IDs.
+    // SDL_JoystickOpen(0) → SDL_OpenJoystick(instance_id).
+    // SDL_JoystickNameForIndex → SDL_GetJoystickNameForID.
+    // SDL_JoystickNum{Axes,Buttons,Balls} → SDL_GetNumJoystick{Axes,Buttons,Balls}.
+    int _joy_count = 0;
+    SDL_JoystickID *_joy_ids = SDL_GetJoysticks(&_joy_count);
+    if (_joy_ids && _joy_count > 0)
     {
-      LOG_WARN("Couldn't open Joystick 0");
+      SDL_JoystickID _first = _joy_ids[0];
+      joy = SDL_OpenJoystick(_first);
+
+      if (joy)
+      {
+        LOG_INFO("Opened Joystick 0");
+        LOG_INFO("Name: {}", SDL_GetJoystickNameForID(_first));
+        LOG_INFO("Number of Axes: {}", SDL_GetNumJoystickAxes(joy));
+        LOG_INFO("Number of Buttons: {}", SDL_GetNumJoystickButtons(joy));
+        LOG_INFO("Number of Balls: {}", SDL_GetNumJoystickBalls(joy));
+      }
+      else
+      {
+        LOG_WARN("Couldn't open Joystick 0");
+      }
     }
+    if (_joy_ids) SDL_free(_joy_ids);
   }
-  if (_joy_ids) SDL_free(_joy_ids);
   return 0;
 }
 
